  "title": "Dental Surgery Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>As a member of the clinical team, you will:</strong></p><ul><li>Provide clinical support to our dentists in the delivery of dental treatment</li><li>Ensure the comfort of patients throughout the treatment, including post-treatment care and follow ups for patients</li><li>Coordinate with the front office staff to ensure a seamless and fuss-free experience for the patients</li><li>Maintain hygiene and sterility standards of instruments, equipment and materials according to procedure</li><li>Provide basic dental laboratory support, e.g. casting of impressions</li><li>Provide customer service for patients at the front desk, including welcoming patients and answering phone calls</li></ul><p><strong>Who are we looking for?</strong></p><p>Someone who:</p><ul><li>has excellent communication skills and good command of English</li><li>has a keen eye for detail, is ready to accept new challenges and willing to learn new things</li><li>Having experience in dental/medical setting, including experience as a dental assistant, will be a plus</li></ul><p>We offer competitive salary and benefits based on your experience and capabilities, and believe in supporting your continuous learning. Training will be provided, where necessary.</p><p>Do you believe that you are the right person for our team, and that we are the right team for you? Send us your detailed resume, expected salary and availability. We would love to hear from you!</p>",
